[ml] Cases called at 9:40AM
Defendant Jamal K Krause-Simmons in court, without counsel. DA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court notes that the Defendant has not been appointed counsel, however the Defendant advises that he wishes to proceed with the Preliminary Hearing today.
After a colloquy with the Defendant, the Court finds that the Defendant's waiver of counsel is appropriate and that the Defendant is able to represent himself today.

The Court proceeds with a Preliminary Hearing on this file:

Lake Mills Officer Brandon Cedarwall WITNESS -sworn & testifies
--direct examination by ADA Hall
--examination by the Court
--cross examination by Mr. Krause-Simmons

The Court finds probable cause that Mr. Krause-Simmons committed a felony. The Court binds him over for Trial.

The Court delays Arraignment to another date and time so that the Defendant may be appointed counsel at the next hearing.
